##A family of seven in Wuhan fights the disease | "as bad as mine, it's getting better. "

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Citizens of Qingshan District, Wuhan, Wuhan, Ms. Xia

The paper's reporter, Sasha Szeto, collates

Xia Lives in Qingshan District, Wuhan, Wuhan. There are seven people in her family: Her in-laws, her parents, her husband, and her three-year-old child. Earlier, the paper reported that seven members of her family were suspected to have contracted new coronary pneumonia.

Her in-laws, her husband has been found lung infection or disease, was admitted to the Ninth Hospital in Wuhan Isolation Ward. Her parents, who also had lung infections, had been treated at a Central Hospital in Wuhan. Subsequently, her in-laws, husband and mother tested positive for the new coronavirus nucleic acid.

Xia's 10 CT examination report showed that "review of the trend for improvement. ".

On the morning of February 4, the 60-year-old father in hospital treatment during the "sudden serious illness" died, she and her family could not see his last face. At the end of January, Ms. Xia was diagnosed with a lung infection. On February 4, she was admitted to a bed waiting for her at Wuhan Central Hospital.

On Feb. 12, Xia said she had tested positive once and negative for nucleic acids in two previous tests. Her husband and three-year-old child are both positive for the latest test results, still need to be hospitalized.

Xia had a good appetite today. She had two boxes for lunch and two boxes for dinner. She was in a good mood, thinking that if something happened, it had to be dealt with. Now that more and more people are coming out of the hospital, she also sees hope.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For lunch and dinner, Xia ate two boxes of rice each. All images in this post are courtesy of Xia

The paper will continue to keep a diary of what Xia's family went through during the treatment.

Here is MS Xia's diary:

Wednesday, February 12 Sunny

Today is my ninth day in the hospital, and I have a routine treatment every day.

Yesterday, my liver function test showed a little abnormal, the doctor for me to add liver protective drugs. Today, my physical indicators are still relatively stable, should enter a stable period, I hope to enter a better period soon.

Recently, my appetite is better, I feel that the hospital lunch box has not filled my stomach. If the nurse has an extra packed lunch, I'll have another. I had two boxes for lunch and dinner.

It's a very debilitating disease. When I used to be healthy, I thought about losing weight every day did not see two taels of meat, now Three Meals a Day to eat, but also eat fruit, I actually thin.

The only downside is that I can't sleep much, especially during the day, when it's obvious that I can't keep up or fall asleep. I thought of a way to put on earphones and blindfolds to listen to light music and close my eyes for rest. If you get more sleep, your body should heal faster.

Today, the doctor said that the nucleic acid test I did on the 7th was positive and on the 10th was negative. The husband and the child are both positive for the latest test results and will continue to be hospitalized.

Today, a friend who has recovered from a new pneumonia told me that she is getting depressed in isolation at home. Living in the hospital, I also enlightened her, I told her my family of seven experience. I said, "it's all right. It's as bad as I am, and it's starting to get better. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ms. Xia counsels her home-quarantined friends.

I have a strong heart, and I encourage my husband when he's really sick. There's no way. It happened. We have to face it. Our panic is more about the new coronavirus unknown, now more and more patients are recovered and discharged from the hospital, we also see hope.

February 12,2020

This issue is edited by Xing Tan
